songs.title: IYKYK

description.plain:
Serving as his second single of 2021, “IYKYK” sees B-Lovee rapping about guns and sex, a topic that seems to be a common motif that runs throughout Lovee’s discography and can be heard on tracks such as “TURNT” and “SHOT DOWN.” On “IYKYK,” B-Lovee raps over an electronic-based beat, something that stands out when compared to other songs previously released, such as “SPOT EM.” “IYKYK” itself is an acronym for “if you know, you know”—a phrase used when someone brings up a prior experience and it’s implied that whomever it’s discussed with immediately understands.

The song itself lyrically may be taking aim at fellow native Bronx rapper Dthang. Dthang originally fired shots at B-Lovee on the Nesty Floxks assisted (and now deleted) track “wedgie man.”
